sql:
SELECT corpus_name, source, language
FROM corpora
WHERE language = 'English' AND source = 'Web';

external_knowledge:
- "treasure chest" metaphorically refers to the database or set of tables;
- "repository" refers to the corpus;
- "precious gem" refers to the word;
- "classification" refers to the part-of-speech tag;
- "value" is a metaphor for degree (frequency, importance) and page rank (relevance, importance);
- "era" refers to the year;
- "miner" represents the user who accessed the data;
- "title" denotes the user's role;
- "way they accessed it" is the access type;
- "spell" represents the search query;
- "glow of their discovery" is the score of the search result;
- "marks they left behind" signifies the annotation;
- "version of the map" refers to the corpus version.

sql:
SELECT corpus_name
FROM corpora
WHERE corpus_id NOT IN (SELECT DISTINCT corpus_id FROM access_logs WHERE access_type = 'download');

SELECT word_id
FROM words
WHERE tag != 'noun';

external_knowledge:
- 'recent past' refers to the year 2017;
- 'specific version' refers to 'v1.0';
- 'special string' refers to the string generated from ASCII codes 'abc';
- 'relevance scores' refer to the score column in the dataset.

sql:
SELECT corpus_name, license
FROM corpora
WHERE corpus_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- 'seeds of language' is a metaphor referring to the words;
- 'fertile soil of the year 2020' metaphorically refers to the corpus in the year 2020;
- 'gardener' is a metaphor representing the user who has contributed to the corpus, in this case, 'Bob Williams'.
